properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 12 at 7:29AM CST until February 12 at 11:00AM CST by NWS Grand Forks ND
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Winter Weather Advisory, snow. Little
additional snow accumulation. Winds gusting as high as 40 mph,
causing blowing snow and visibilities less than half a mile.
For the Wind Chill Advisory, very cold wind chills expected.
Wind chills as low as 40 below zero.

* WHERE...The Roseau to Thief River Falls corridor.

* WHEN...For the Winter Weather Advisory, until 11 AM CST this
morning. For the Wind Chill Advisory, from 11 AM this morning
to 3 PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Areas of blowing snow will significantly reduce the
visibility. The hazardous conditions will impact the morning
commute. The dangerously cold wind chills could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

The latest road conditions for North Dakota can be found at
dot.nd.gov/travel and for Minnesota at 511mn.org, or by calling
5 1 1 in either state.
